{'project_name': 'Improved cropland management project in Bwzho', 'project_summary': 'The “Improved cropland management project in Bwzho” developed by Guangxi Meiluo Agriculture Science and Technology Co., Ltd. aims to raise farmer’s awareness on the benefits of sustainable agriculture and how to change the agricultural practices to help in climate change mitigation and adaptation. The project will assist farmers to overcome barriers that prevent adoption of improved agricultural land management practices and provide technical assistance where needed. The objective of the project is to reduce emissions from agricultural practices and increase soil carbon storage, in order to achieve these, a package of practices that change the pre-existing agricultural management activities will be carried out, the specific activities are one or combination of the following:
Reduced fertilizer(organic or inorganic) application;
Improved water management/irrigation;
Reduced tillage/improved residue management;
The project activity will cover Baise city and Hechi city, which are within the boundary of Guangxi Autonomous Region, a southern province in China. Prior to the start of the implementation of the project, there was no similar sequestration of carbon, removals or net reduction of GHG activities. The baseline scenario is the continuation of pre-project agricultural land management practices, which are common agricultural practices in the project area. Over the 20 years of the first crediting period, the project will generate an estimated annual average removal and reduction of 80,000 tCO2e.', 'project_state_province': 'Guangxi Province', 'project_country': 'China', 'project_latitude': 22.85, 'project_longitude': 108.22}
